                  <h4>Portfolio Project (2025-2026) • Singapore</h4>
                </div>
                <span class="timeline-date">★ Portfolio Project</span>
              </div>
              <p class="tech-stack">Tech Stack: Python • FastAPI • LangGraph • CrewAI • OpenAI Agents SDK • Claude API • MCP • Telegram Bot API • WhatsApp Business API • ChromaDB • Redis • pgvector • PostgreSQL • Playwright • Docker • AWS Bedrock • ReactJS • WebSocket Streaming • Guardrails AI • LangSmith</p>
              <p class="timeline-details">Inspired by OpenClaw's agentic architecture — built a production-grade, message-driven multi-agent platform that converts natural language instructions from messaging channels into decomposed, executable task plans using stateful AI agents.</p>
              <ul class="timeline-list">
                <li><strong>AGENTIC CORE:</strong> Designed LangGraph-based orchestration engine that receives messages via Telegram/WhatsApp, decomposes high-level goals into structured sub-tasks, and assigns each sub-task to specialized agents (Researcher, Executor, Validator, Summarizer) — mirroring OpenClaw's 4-tier architecture.</li>
                <li><strong>MCP INTEGRATION:</strong> Implemented Model Context Protocol (MCP) to expose business tools (calendar, email, file system, shell commands) as discoverable agent capabilities; agents dynamically invoke tools based on task context without hardcoded logic.</li>
                <li><strong>MULTI-AGENT ORCHESTRATION:</strong> Built CrewAI-based role-based agent teams for domain tasks — a Finance Agent crew for report generation, a DevOps Agent crew for deployment validation, and a Research Agent crew for real-time web data gathering using browser automation (Playwright).</li>
                <li><strong>PERSISTENT MEMORY:</strong> Implemented layered agent memory using Redis (short-term session context), ChromaDB vector store (long-term semantic recall), and pgvector (structured knowledge retrieval) — enabling agents to remember user preferences and past task outcomes across sessions.</li>
                <li><strong>REAL-TIME STREAMING:</strong> Built WebSocket-based streaming response layer so users see agent reasoning steps and task progress live in the Telegram/WhatsApp interface as tasks execute.</li>
                <li><strong>AI SECURITY LAYER:</strong> Integrated Guardrails AI for prompt injection detection, role-based tool permission enforcement, and human-in-the-loop approval gates for high-risk actions — preventing agent hijacking attacks.</li>
                <li><strong>OBSERVABILITY:</strong> Wired LangSmith for full agent trace logging, tool call auditing, latency tracking, and token cost dashboards; alerting via Slack webhook for failed agent workflows.</li>
                <li><strong>RESULT:</strong> End-to-end agent workflow completes in under 8 seconds for standard 3-step tasks; system handles 200+ concurrent agent sessions on a 2-vCPU AWS EC2 instance.</li>
