              <p class="timeline-details">Production-grade RAG platform purpose-built for Singapore's financial and legal sectors — ingests complex documents and delivers precise, cited AI answers with stateful multi-turn reasoning.</p>
              <ul class="timeline-list">
                <li><strong>ADVANCED RAG PIPELINE:</strong> Built hybrid search RAG using Pinecone dense vector search + BM25 keyword search with cross-encoder reranking — achieving 94% answer relevancy vs 71% with naive RAG.</li>
                <li><strong>LANGGRAPH REASONING AGENT:</strong> Implemented LangGraph stateful reasoning loop — agent classifies query intent, decides retrieval strategy, validates source confidence, then synthesizes cited answers with source footnotes.</li>
                <li><strong>MULTI-DOCUMENT COMPARISON:</strong> Built agentic document comparison workflow — upload two contracts/policies, agent identifies clause-level differences, highlights risk areas, and generates structured comparison reports.</li>
                <li><strong>AWS BEDROCK INTEGRATION:</strong> Deployed Claude Sonnet 3.7 via AWS Bedrock as primary inference engine; implemented intelligent model routing — cutting API costs by 38% while maintaining quality.</li>
                <li><strong>SPRING AI MICROSERVICE:</strong> Exposed RAG capabilities as a Java Spring AI microservice with typed tool definitions — allowing existing Java enterprise systems to call AI document analysis via standard REST/gRPC.</li>
                <li><strong>FINE-TUNED EMBEDDINGS:</strong> Fine-tuned HuggingFace embedding model on Singapore financial terminology corpus — improved embedding precision for domain terms by 22%.</li>
                <li><strong>MLOPS PIPELINE:</strong> Built MLflow experiment tracking, LangSmith for RAG chain tracing, and W&B for retrieval quality dashboards; automated model promotion via GitLab CI.</li>
                <li><strong>RESULT:</strong> Platform processes 10,000+ document pages, serves 1,200+ daily queries, returns cited answers in under 3 seconds; deployed on Kubernetes with 99.95% uptime SLA.</li>
